<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-21T11:50:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1689" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1689">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.93/112.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Hostetter</persName>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Hermosillo</hi></placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1915-05-21T11:50:00-05:00" notBefore="1915-05-06T00:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">not
                                            dated</hi></date><hi rend="italic">; received May 21,
                                        1915—11.50 a.m.</hi>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Rabble are sacking the Chinese stores at present moment, and although
                                prefecto is doing what he can do not believe he is strong enough to
                                stop the same. Have wired governor to order troops here.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hostetter.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>